# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0
# Trustfile — Trust boundaries and integrity invariants for Cliodynamics.jl
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell <j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>
#
# Defines what LLM/SLM agents are trusted to do without asking, and
# integrity invariants that verify the repo has not been tampered with.
#
# NOTE (2026-06-13): identity + trust-deny-areas localized for Cliodynamics.jl.
# The estate-carried file named rsr-template-repo and scoped deny-areas to
# "template files"; the integrity invariants below are kept and apply to
# Cliodynamics.jl.

[metadata]
name = "Cliodynamics.jl-trustfile"
project = "Cliodynamics.jl"
schema_version = "1.0"

@abstract:
Trust boundaries and integrity checks for Cliodynamics.jl. Defines what AI
agents may do autonomously and what requires human approval, plus checks that
verify repository integrity.
@end

## Trust Levels

Cliodynamics.jl operates at trust level: standard

Trust levels:
- maximal:    Agent may read, build, test, lint, format, heal freely. Only destructive/external actions require approval.
- standard:   Agent may read, build, test, lint, format. Edits to semantic-authority surfaces and workflows need approval.
- restricted: Agent may read and build. All modifications need approval.
- minimal:    Agent may read specific files only.

Current trust level: standard
Rationale: Cliodynamics.jl is a published Julia library; the single-file
design (ADR-002) and mathematical model implementations are protected surfaces
that require careful literature-grounded review, so full autonomy is scoped
below "maximal".

## Integrity Invariants

### Secrets

#### no-secrets-committed
- description: No credential files in repo
- run: test ! -f .env && test ! -f credentials.json && test ! -f .env.local && test ! -f .env.production
- severity: critical

#### no-private-keys
- description: No private key files committed
- run: "! find . -name '*.pem' -o -name '*.key' -o -name 'id_rsa' -o -name 'id_ed25519' 2>/dev/null | grep -v target | head -1 | grep -q ."
- severity: critical

#### no-tokens-in-source
- description: No hardcoded API tokens in source
- run: "! grep -rE '(api[_-]?key|secret|token|password)\\s*[:=]\\s*[\"'\''\\[A-Za-z0-9]{16,}' --include='*.jl' --include='*.zig' . 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q ."
- severity: critical
- notes: FARM_DISPATCH_TOKEN is referenced by NAME only (see bot_directives/git-private-farm.a2ml), never by value

## Provenance

#### author-correct
- description: Git author matches expected identity
- run: "git log -1 --format='%ae' | grep -qE '(hyperpolymath|j\\.d\\.a\\.jewell)'"
- severity: warning

#### license-content
- description: LICENSE is MPL-2.0 (Palimpsest)
- run: grep -q 'Mozilla Public License\|MPL-2.0' LICENSE
- severity: warning

## Cliodynamics.jl-Specific Trust

### semantic-authority-protected
- description: Semantic-authority surfaces require explicit approval to change
- run: echo "Protected: src/Cliodynamics.jl (model implementations), ffi/zig/, src/abi/, .claude/CLAUDE.md, .github/workflows/"
- severity: advisory
- areas:
  - src/Cliodynamics.jl
  - ffi/zig/
  - src/abi/
  - .claude/CLAUDE.md
  - .github/workflows/

### single-file-design-protected
- description: ADR-002 single-file design must not be split without explicit maintainer decision
- run: "! find src/ -name '*.jl' | grep -v 'Cliodynamics.jl' | head -1 | grep -q ."
- severity: advisory
- notes: Extensions under ext/ are expected and correct; additional src/*.jl files are not

## Container Security

#### container-images-pinned
- description: Containerfile uses pinned base images
- run: test ! -f Containerfile || grep -q 'cgr.dev\|@sha256:' Containerfile
- severity: warning

#### no-dockerfile
- description: No Dockerfile (use Containerfile)
- run: test ! -f Dockerfile
- severity: warning
